-- New Zealand Defeats Pakistan by Five Wickets in Twenty20 Cricket Match
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2010-12-26T13:36:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-26/new-zealand-defeats-pakistan-by-five-wickets-in-twenty20-cricket-match.html
Tim Southee took a hat-trick as New
Zealand beat Pakistan by five wickets in the opening Twenty20
cricket international in Auckland.  Southee helped the hosts restrict Pakistan to 143-9, with
New Zealand reaching 146-5 in reply with 17 balls to spare.
Martin Guptill cracked 54 from 29 balls for New Zealand.  The three-match series continues in Hamilton on Dec. 28,
with the final match in Christchurch two days later. The teams
then play two Tests and six one-day internationals.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  